  "prompt": "What universities does Viad recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Viad is a company that operates in the travel, tourism, and experiential services sectors. While specific details about their recruitment strategies for new graduates might not be publicly available, companies like Viad typically recruit from a variety of universities and majors depending on their business needs.\n\n**Universities:**\nViad may target a range of universities, including but not limited to:\n- Large public universities with strong business, hospitality, and tourism programs.\n- Private institutions known for their business and marketing programs.\n- Universities with strong engineering and technology programs if they are looking to fill technical roles.\n\nExamples might include:\n- Arizona State University\n- University of Arizona\n- University of Nevada, Las Vegas (UNLV)\n- University of Colorado Boulder\n- University of Southern California (USC)\n- Cornell University\n\n**Majors:**\nGiven Viad's focus areas, they might look for graduates in the following majors:\n- Hospitality Management\n- Tourism Management\n- Business Administration\n- Marketing\n- Event Management\n- Finance\n- Engineering (if they have technical roles related to their experiential services)\n- Information Technology\n\nFor precise information, it's best to check Viad's career page or contact their HR department directly, as recruitment strategies can change and may vary based on the specific needs of the company at any given time.",
